{{quote|"Now thou shalt go at last to Gondolin, Turgon; and I will maintain my power in the Vale of Sirion, and in all the waters therein, so that none shall mark thy going, nor shall any find there the hidden entrance against thy will."|[[Ulmo]], ''[[Quenta Silmarillion]]'', "[[Of the Noldor in Beleriand]]"}}
The '''Vale(s) of Sirion''' was the wide valley of the River [[Sirion]], that separated [[West Beleriand]] from [[East Beleriand]].<ref>{{CH|6}}, p. 109</ref> The term seems to apply especially to that part of the river's course around the [[Pass of Sirion]]<ref>{{CH|12}}, p. 190</ref> that lay to the north of [[Doriath]].<ref>{{S|Beleriand}}</ref>

These waters were protected by [[Ulmo]]<ref>{{S|Noldor}}</ref> until some point prior to {{FA|495}}; at that time, two messengers from [[Círdan]] bore tidings to [[Orodreth]] that the Evil of the North had defiled the springs of Sirion, and Ulmo's power had withdrawn.<ref>{{S|Turin}}</ref>


